<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="301" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="301">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="301">
This species was reported from dry lichen communities on granite outcrops on a lake margin in NS (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka, CG" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="66" pageNumber="331" pagination="325 - 327" publicationUrl="10.4039/n03-113" refId="B27" refString="Majka, CG, 2005. New records of Melyridae (Coleoptera) from the Maritime Provinces of Canada. The Canadian Entomologist 137: 325 - 327, DOI: 10.4039/n03-113" title="New records of Melyridae (Coleoptera) from the Maritime Provinces of Canada." url="10.4039/n03-113" volume="137" year="2005">Majka 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens from NB were found on a granitic bald on a sun-exposed bare rock face. The bright-colored adults were observed crawling over the surface of the lichen-covered rockface in full sun.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
